{
  "texts": [
    "Despite Turnitin's role in maintaining academic integrity, it faces ethical and educational issues.",
    "The opacity of Turnitin's algorithm and database content prevents users from knowing how their work is processed and compared.",
    "Over-reliance on such tools by schools might stifle students' creative thinking, just as excessive supervision might limit their ability to explore and learn independently.",
    "Educational institutions should use Turnitin while also providing educational guidance, emphasizing not only the consequences of plagiarism but also teaching proper citation practices and independent thinking to ensure students understand the importance of academic integrity.",
    "Turnitin should be part of a broader academic integrity education plan rather than the sole regulatory tool."
  ]
}